 intellectual interest across Europe - was racked between commercialism and 'art'. A number of the major films are studied in detail: Le Double amour (Epstein, 1925), Feu Mathias Pascal (L'Herbier, 1925), Éducation de prince (Diamant-Berger, 1927), Le Joueur d'échecs (Bernard, 1927), La Sirène des tropiques (Etiévant and Nalpas, 1927), Les Deux timides (Clair, 1928), Un chien andalou (Buñuel, 1929), Monte-Cristo (Fescourt, 1929), and Baroud (Ingram, 1932). Key FeaturesThe first major study of a French silent cinema star.Provides an in-depth analysis of star performance.Includes extensive appendices of documents from popular cinema magazines of the period. "  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMotion picture actors and actressesxFrance. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszFrance. 0aSilent filmsxHistory and criticismxFrance. 0aSilent filmszFrancexHistory and criticism. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Radio / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aRebillard, Eric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074862197240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748629602?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748629602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748629602/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK